The paper is about mapping and localization in robotics, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The use of lidar scans and feature extraction from geometry suggests Computer Vision (cs.CV) as another likely category. The proposed approach also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under categories such as Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for evaluating the proposed approach, which could suggest Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as a possible category.
